1
00:00:13,068 --> 00:00:17,3
[drink being poured]

2
00:00:21,022 --> 00:00:22,7
Forgive me, Father...

3
00:00:23,027 --> 00:00:24,7
for not offering you a drink.

4
00:00:25,073 --> 00:00:28,6
I have an aversion to the cloth. 
Daddy issues.

5
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:29,7
Long story.

6
00:00:29,082 --> 00:00:33,8
I understand, and I do apologize
for the intrusion, Mr. Morningstar.

7
00:00:34,065 --> 00:00:36,2
Please allow me to explain myself.

8
00:00:36,053 --> 00:00:37,9
Excellent course of action.

9
00:00:38,053 --> 00:00:41,1
You see, I'm not a normal priest.

10
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:43,7
[laughing] Was there ever such a thing?

11
00:00:44,008 --> 00:00:45,9
I mean I'm not a normal priest
in the sense

12
00:00:46,004 --> 00:00:48,2
that I don't have my own congregation.

13
00:00:49,025 --> 00:00:50,1
I am a...

14
00:00:50,092 --> 00:00:51,9
I'm an investigator.

15
00:00:52,084 --> 00:00:53,6
For the Vatican.

16
00:00:56,063 --> 00:00:58,0
Vatican investigator?

17
00:00:58,051 --> 00:01:00,6
Sounds like a soon-to-be-canceled
TV show.

18
00:01:00,097 --> 00:01:02,7
I assure you, it's a very real job.

19
00:01:03,027 --> 00:01:06,6
I've spent the last 40 years traveling
the globe in pursuit of the demonic.

20
00:01:07,090 --> 00:01:09,2
I know the divine is real.

21
00:01:09,094 --> 00:01:12,3
And I also know that evil walks the earth.

22
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:14,1
And that you, Mr. Morningstar--

23
00:01:14,028 --> 00:01:16,0
Oh, brother, here we go.

24
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:17,0
Are not it.

25
00:01:19,095 --> 00:01:21,5
Not quite what I was expecting.

26
00:01:22,083 --> 00:01:26,3
So if I'm not the devil,
then why are you here?

27
00:01:26,087 --> 00:01:29,2
And what does any of this
have to do with the Detective?

28
00:01:29,038 --> 00:01:31,3
Because Miss Decker believes that you are.

29
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:33,6
I see.

30
00:01:33,071 --> 00:01:36,8
About a month ago, she came to Rome
with a most outlandish tale.

31
00:01:37,084 --> 00:01:40,2
The devil himself
is hiding in plain sight,

32
00:01:40,030 --> 00:01:43,3
masquerading as a nightclub owner
in Los Angeles,

33
00:01:43,043 --> 00:01:46,7
and that he'd revealed himself to her.

34
00:01:48,010 --> 00:01:48,9
Well...

35
00:01:49,031 --> 00:01:50,6
this is wonderful news.

36
00:01:50,090 --> 00:01:52,1
Wonderful? How so?

37
00:01:52,019 --> 00:01:55,1
Well, as my therapist would say--
I know, so LA...

38
00:01:55,069 --> 00:01:58,2
But she'd say
that talking about your issues

39
00:01:58,028 --> 00:01:59,9
was the first step in dealing with them,

40
00:02:00,003 --> 00:02:02,4
so if the Detective did have issues
with me...

41
00:02:03,003 --> 00:02:04,4
sounds like they've been dealt with.

42
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:08,0
Now, if that's everything, Father,
you can be on your merry way.

43
00:02:08,008 --> 00:02:11,0
I just felt that it was my duty 
to warn you.

44
00:02:12,013 --> 00:02:14,9
Because the reason that she came to Rome
was to, well...

45
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:17,2
send the devil back to hell.

46
00:02:17,047 --> 00:02:18,3
[laughs]

47
00:02:19,068 --> 00:02:20,9
The Detective would never do that.

48
00:02:21,026 --> 00:02:23,2
Chloe is a good person with a good heart.

49
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:25,3
Finally, something we can agree on.

50
00:02:25,043 --> 00:02:28,4
But whatever she went through,
whatever drove her to Rome...

51
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:30,5
it shook her to her very core.

52
00:02:32,027 --> 00:02:34,1
She's the reason that I'm here.

53
00:02:36,019 --> 00:02:39,3
You need to be careful, Mr. Morningstar.

54
00:02:41,003 --> 00:02:42,9
God knows what she has planned for you.

55
00:02:55,067 --> 00:03:00,0
[humming quietly]

56
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:04,3
[Ella]
What are you so cheery about, Decker?

57
00:03:04,043 --> 00:03:05,2
What?

58
00:03:05,068 --> 00:03:07,9
-I'm not cheery.
-Wait, why aren't you cheery?

59
00:03:08,002 --> 00:03:10,0
I've been nursing a bad one all day.

60
00:03:10,039 --> 00:03:12,4
Ha! What? Too much Romulan ale?

61
00:03:12,052 --> 00:03:13,8
Too much tequila.

62
00:03:14,044 --> 00:03:17,4
I went a little nutso
on all the margeritas yesterday.

63
00:03:17,086 --> 00:03:21,3
Yesterday, Sunday...
Did you swap out the sacramental wine?

64
00:03:21,065 --> 00:03:23,3
I skipped church yesterday.

65
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:25,0
And the week before, you said.

66
00:03:26,028 --> 00:03:29,5
Listen, Ella,
I sort of wanted to check in with you,

67
00:03:30,021 --> 00:03:32,1
-to see--
-You know, it's just...

68
00:03:32,058 --> 00:03:34,8
me and the big guy
are on a bit of a break.

69
00:03:34,092 --> 00:03:38,0
I completely... understand.
I mean, more than you'll ever know.

70
00:03:38,017 --> 00:03:39,1
In fact...

71
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:40,5
recently...

72
00:03:41,001 --> 00:03:43,9
I got clarity on a very similar issue.

73
00:03:44,068 --> 00:03:45,5
And...

74
00:03:46,014 --> 00:03:48,3
I think it's why I've been feeling
so positive lately.

75
00:03:48,051 --> 00:03:49,7
-[bang]
-[man's voice] Enough!

76
00:03:49,085 --> 00:03:51,1
Stop calling me!

77
00:03:52,048 --> 00:03:53,3
Jeez.

78
00:03:54,010 --> 00:03:54,9
Hang on.

79
00:03:55,065 --> 00:03:56,6
Is everything okay?

80
00:03:56,090 --> 00:03:58,1
[phone buzzes]

81
00:03:58,019 --> 00:03:59,5
-Everything's fine.
-[phone buzzes]

82
00:03:59,082 --> 00:04:01,4
Well, are you going to answer that?

83
00:04:01,053 --> 00:04:02,4
Absolutely not.

84
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:03,9
Dan, it could be important.

85
00:04:04,061 --> 00:04:05,6
Be my guest.

86
00:04:06,032 --> 00:04:07,1
Okay.

87
00:04:08,012 --> 00:04:08,9
Dan's phone.

88
00:04:09,004 --> 00:04:10,8
[gurgling roar on phone]

89
00:04:12,075 --> 00:04:13,6
What the hell is that?

90
00:04:14,092 --> 00:04:16,2
I'll show you what that was.

91
00:04:18,071 --> 00:04:19,7
Yeah.

92
00:04:20,013 --> 00:04:21,1
That's my phone number.

93
00:04:22,013 --> 00:04:24,5
Lucifer's been posting these
all over the precinct.

94
00:04:25,064 --> 00:04:26,8
It's not funny, Chloe.

95
00:04:27,047 --> 00:04:29,1
I swear he only exists to...

96
00:04:30,006 --> 00:04:30,8
torture me.

97
00:04:31,077 --> 00:04:35,0
Look, I know you and Lucifer
have had your issues lately,

98
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,9
but maybe this is his way of--

99
00:04:36,098 --> 00:04:39,5
Know what? I'm sick and tired
of everybody making excuses for him.

100
00:04:40,028 --> 00:04:43,1
I wish you could just see
a little bit of what I see, Chloe.

101
00:04:44,074 --> 00:04:45,5
He's...

102
00:04:46,061 --> 00:04:48,0
he's a bad guy.

103
00:04:48,066 --> 00:04:49,5
He's...

104
00:04:50,054 --> 00:04:51,6
he's trying to be better.

105
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:54,2
He... in his own way.

106
00:04:54,083 --> 00:04:55,6
[Dan] Whatever.

107
00:05:01,055 --> 00:05:04,7
[ambient pop playing in the background]

108
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:10,9
Brother.

109
00:05:11,043 --> 00:05:12,7
You look like I feel.

110
00:05:12,085 --> 00:05:16,3
No, I'm pretty sure that my issues
are much bigger than yours. Trust me.

111
00:05:16,044 --> 00:05:18,5
I think we all know
nothing is bigger than mine.

112
00:05:19,006 --> 00:05:21,1
-The strangest thing just happened--
-Linda's pregnant.

113
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:24,8
We'll call it a tie. [chuckles]

114
00:05:26,003 --> 00:05:27,3
Are you sure it's yours?

115
00:05:27,045 --> 00:05:28,8
Lucy, Linda's not like that.

116
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:30,5
You of all people should know.

117
00:05:30,066 --> 00:05:32,3
Relax, brother, I just meant...

118
00:05:32,095 --> 00:05:35,2
a celestial impregnating a human--

119
00:05:35,071 --> 00:05:36,7
How is it even possible?

120
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:39,4
And, if it is,
how has this not already happened to you?

121
00:05:39,092 --> 00:05:41,0
[Lucifer] True.

122
00:05:41,088 --> 00:05:42,7
Mm.

123
00:05:44,001 --> 00:05:45,7
Maybe there's another explanation.

124
00:05:46,001 --> 00:05:48,1
You think Linda's an angel in disguise,
don't you?

125
00:05:48,026 --> 00:05:50,7
I've been wondering the same thing.
Maybe she's not even human.

126
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:55,3
Or, maybe, when you lost your wings,
you became as mortal as it gets.

127
00:05:55,085 --> 00:05:58,1
Maybe you became more human
than you realized.

128
00:05:59,002 --> 00:05:59,8
Oh.

129
00:06:00,015 --> 00:06:01,4
Probably makes more sense.

130
00:06:01,052 --> 00:06:02,4
[Lucifer laughs]

131
00:06:02,057 --> 00:06:04,6
I bet you regret coming back now,
eh, brother?

132
00:06:04,073 --> 00:06:07,3
Absolutely not.
Quite the opposite in fact.

133
00:06:07,061 --> 00:06:10,7
Oh, come on, you don't have to sell me.
You can join the Navy for all I care.

134
00:06:10,087 --> 00:06:12,7
Lucy, I am happy to be here.

135
00:06:13,091 --> 00:06:15,5
Don't you see? I'm going to be a father.

136
00:06:17,012 --> 00:06:20,0
Well, if you're so happy, then
what are you doing hiding out in my bar?

137
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:22,6
Because I have absolutely no idea
what to do.

138
00:06:24,013 --> 00:06:25,0
I mean...

139
00:06:26,026 --> 00:06:27,3
where do I even begin?

140
00:06:27,047 --> 00:06:29,0
Wrong tree, I'm afraid.

141
00:06:29,084 --> 00:06:33,6
But you are here on Earth,
so, if it's any consolation,

142
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:35,4
you couldn't do worse than our father.

143
00:06:35,081 --> 00:06:39,0
-How do you know that?
-Because ours was literally never there.

144
00:06:42,048 --> 00:06:44,3
-Hey, where've you been?
-What do you mean?

145
00:06:44,073 --> 00:06:47,3
Well, I sent you that text
about rescheduling our date.

146
00:06:47,044 --> 00:06:50,4
Oh, yes, right.
Definitely, no, I'd like that.

147
00:06:50,049 --> 00:06:52,2
Okay, great. Good.

148
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:54,1
Is everything okay?

149
00:06:54,033 --> 00:06:57,5
Yes, just feeling a little parched
and my flask has apparently disappeared.

150
00:06:57,058 --> 00:06:58,7
You know, I've been thinking.

151
00:06:59,046 --> 00:07:01,6
Maybe it's best
if you don't drink so much.

152
00:07:02,042 --> 00:07:04,1
You know, at least while we're working.

153
00:07:04,021 --> 00:07:05,0
Ah.

154
00:07:05,038 --> 00:07:06,5
I see what this is about.

155
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,7
-You do?
-Yes.

156
00:07:07,084 --> 00:07:09,5
And you needn't worry, Detective.

157
00:07:09,063 --> 00:07:13,1
Unbelievable as it may seem, being
the actual devil does have its downsides.

158
00:07:13,059 --> 00:07:15,8
I can't get drunk on normal,
human amounts of alcohol.

159
00:07:16,031 --> 00:07:17,8
I only drink because I like the taste.

160
00:07:17,089 --> 00:07:19,8
Well, I'm... but people don't know that.
[laughs]

161
00:07:20,052 --> 00:07:22,1
What do I care what other people think?

162
00:07:22,023 --> 00:07:24,4
I'm just saying showing people
that you can change is--

163
00:07:24,052 --> 00:07:26,0
Ah, here it is!

164
00:07:26,023 --> 00:07:27,1
[laughs]

165
00:07:27,044 --> 00:07:28,4
Wrong pocket.

166
00:07:29,024 --> 00:07:30,1
Shall we?

167
00:07:31,024 --> 00:07:33,9
[camera shutter clicks]

168
00:07:34,024 --> 00:07:36,1
Hey, Ella. Are you feeling better today?

169
00:07:36,024 --> 00:07:38,1
[Ella sighs]
Well, better than this poor girl.

170
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:43,6
Susan Ochoa, 29. A bona fide
rocket scientist at Brody Aerospace.

171
00:07:44,029 --> 00:07:47,3
Neighbor saw the door open,
body on the floor, called it in.

172
00:07:47,063 --> 00:07:49,6
-I'm assuming that's the murder weapon.
-Yep.

173
00:07:49,076 --> 00:07:51,4
A good old knife in the back.

174
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:52,8
Bit on the nose.

175
00:07:54,009 --> 00:07:55,4
So no forced entry...

176
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:57,4
two glasses,

177
00:07:57,056 --> 00:07:58,7
someone brought flowers.

178
00:07:59,014 --> 00:08:00,4
She knew her attacker.

179
00:08:00,052 --> 00:08:03,5
It's always the ones you least suspect,
the ones you trust the most,

180
00:08:03,081 --> 00:08:04,7
that hurt you.

181
00:08:05,027 --> 00:08:08,5
[Ella] They wait until your guard is down
and then wham!

182
00:08:09,028 --> 00:08:10,6
In my case, it was tequila.

183
00:08:11,011 --> 00:08:11,9
Riveting.

184
00:08:13,024 --> 00:08:14,1
Any witnesses?

185
00:08:14,032 --> 00:08:16,4
None, but the victim's friend
might know more.

186
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,1
Oscar.

187
00:08:19,004 --> 00:08:22,2
Do you know anyone who would have wanted
to hurt Susan, Mr. Rivas?

188
00:08:23,012 --> 00:08:24,9
No. Everybody liked Susan.

189
00:08:25,004 --> 00:08:26,6
Who did she trust the most?

190
00:08:26,075 --> 00:08:29,6
To be honest, I don't know much 
about Susan's life here.

191
00:08:29,075 --> 00:08:32,9
I just came from El Salvador. She was
supposed to pick me up from the airport.

192
00:08:33,001 --> 00:08:34,8
When she didn't show, I came here and...

193
00:08:36,022 --> 00:08:37,1
I saw all of this.

194
00:08:37,035 --> 00:08:39,3
-And how do you know her?
-[Oscar] We were in a gang.

195
00:08:40,035 --> 00:08:41,2
Los Xs.

196
00:08:41,031 --> 00:08:45,0
A gang member turned rocket scientist.
Gosh, and I thought I had range.

197
00:08:45,027 --> 00:08:47,4
When I left the life,
I wanted to pay it forward.

198
00:08:47,052 --> 00:08:50,1
So I helped people like Susan
get out and get clean.

199
00:08:50,023 --> 00:08:51,4
She was a drug addict?

200
00:08:51,086 --> 00:08:53,7
Don't judge her. A lot of us were.

201
00:08:53,086 --> 00:08:55,7
Oh, I'm not judging. I love drugs.

202
00:08:55,078 --> 00:08:58,2
In fact, do you think she might have any
lying around? [giggles]

203
00:08:58,037 --> 00:09:01,7
Do you know if Susan
still had any connection to Los Xs?

204
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:03,2
No, she made a clean break.

205
00:09:03,037 --> 00:09:07,0
She moved here, went to school,
made an amazing life for herself.

206
00:09:10,029 --> 00:09:12,6
Promise me you will punish
the son of a bitch that did this.

207
00:09:12,071 --> 00:09:13,5
Oh...

208
00:09:14,013 --> 00:09:15,0
with pleasure.

209
00:09:15,068 --> 00:09:18,8
Okay. Thank you, Mr. Rivas.
We'll be in touch if we need anything.

210
00:09:18,093 --> 00:09:22,1
You take him. Let's get in touch with
next of kin and head back to the precinct.

211
00:09:22,018 --> 00:09:23,3
I meant what I said earlier.

212
00:09:23,072 --> 00:09:24,6
What do you mean?

213
00:09:24,068 --> 00:09:27,2
That I don't care
what people think about me.

214
00:09:27,094 --> 00:09:32,2
So if you want to talk to anyone about,
you know, me being the devil... [laughs]

215
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:36,0
That is if you haven't already, then,
just know that it is totally fine with me.

216
00:09:36,070 --> 00:09:39,2
Okay. I don't think that's necessary.

217
00:09:39,028 --> 00:09:41,7
Right.
So you haven't told anyone about me?

218
00:09:42,037 --> 00:09:43,2
No.

219
00:09:43,079 --> 00:09:44,9
No, not a soul.

220
00:10:00,051 --> 00:10:01,8
[female] She's a monster.

221
00:10:02,026 --> 00:10:04,7
Demanding, complains all the time.

222
00:10:05,022 --> 00:10:07,5
It's like nothing is ever good enough.

223
00:10:07,081 --> 00:10:10,4
And how old is Brooklyn now?

224
00:10:10,081 --> 00:10:16,1
Three. You know, sometimes I catch her
looking at me like she knows she's won.

225
00:10:16,028 --> 00:10:17,9
It can't be all bad.

226
00:10:18,074 --> 00:10:20,0
-Can it?
-Don't you get it?

227
00:10:20,011 --> 00:10:21,3
She's a sociopath.

228
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:24,1
Children are all sociopaths.

229
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,0
[door opens]

230
00:10:25,012 --> 00:10:26,5
[Lucifer sighs] Time's up.

231
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:29,1
Apologies, I've more pressing matters
to discuss with the doctor.

232
00:10:29,021 --> 00:10:30,9
I'm in the middle of my session here.

233
00:10:31,004 --> 00:10:34,1
Well, the doctor is with child.
She needs her rest.

234
00:10:34,025 --> 00:10:36,4
How dare you burden her
with your petty concerns, now?

235
00:10:36,051 --> 00:10:37,7
Run along. Come on, shoo!

236
00:10:37,097 --> 00:10:39,3
-[patient squeaks]
-Shoo.

237
00:10:39,072 --> 00:10:41,7
-[patient squeaks]
-[door bangs]

238
00:10:42,009 --> 00:10:43,0
So...

239
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:45,4
I hear congratulations are in order.

240
00:10:45,056 --> 00:10:48,5
Some people claim
to find the life-long burden fulfilling.

241
00:10:48,081 --> 00:10:51,8
I'd rather not talk about the pregnancy
at work, if you don't mind.

242
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,6
Lips sealed. So, about me...

243
00:10:55,032 --> 00:10:58,0
What do you do
when someone has betrayed you?

244
00:10:58,015 --> 00:11:01,5
Normally I'd go straight to punishment,
fire, brimstone,

245
00:11:01,066 --> 00:11:03,3
public humiliation via YouTube.

246
00:11:03,045 --> 00:11:06,6
But in this case,
the subject happens to be none other...

247
00:11:07,020 --> 00:11:08,3
than the Detective.

248
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:09,2
Wait, Chloe?

249
00:11:09,079 --> 00:11:10,6
What did she do?

250
00:11:10,071 --> 00:11:12,4
I caught her in a lie.

251
00:11:13,004 --> 00:11:15,7
A most heinous transgression.

252
00:11:16,034 --> 00:11:18,6
Oh, and she may be plotting
to send me back to hell.

253
00:11:18,076 --> 00:11:21,3
Okay, that's a very serious accusation.

254
00:11:22,026 --> 00:11:24,7
-How do you know this?
-A complete stranger told me.

255
00:11:26,035 --> 00:11:27,9
Have you talked to Chloe about this?

256
