508
00:23:01,092 --> 00:23:05,9
It's very kind of you and I appreciate
the gesture, I really do...

509
00:23:07,017 --> 00:23:08,0
but I...

510
00:23:10,005 --> 00:23:12,7
I told you you were the father
because you deserved to know.

511
00:23:14,001 --> 00:23:16,2
Not to pressure you into helping out.

512
00:23:16,056 --> 00:23:18,6
The truth is
I'm used to doing things on my own.

513
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:22,3
I don't see why raising a baby
should be any different.

514
00:23:23,061 --> 00:23:24,6
I just wanted to help.

515
00:23:24,094 --> 00:23:26,2
You don't need to worry about me.

516
00:23:28,082 --> 00:23:29,9
And you, I...

517
00:23:30,065 --> 00:23:31,7
I would love to talk, but,

518
00:23:31,086 --> 00:23:35,1
unfortunately, I have a ton of paperwork
to do before my next client, so...

519
00:23:35,041 --> 00:23:36,2
Right.

520
00:23:38,020 --> 00:23:39,3
I'll get out of your way.

521
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,0
I like that one.

522
00:23:49,034 --> 00:23:51,2
[Maze]
Really? Not the one I would have chosen,

523
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:53,3
but you are the closest person to a baby
I know.

524
00:23:54,043 --> 00:23:57,0
Okay, so at what age did your parents
teach you to hunt?

525
00:23:57,014 --> 00:24:00,0
[Dan] What's going on? Maze, you know
she's not allowed to play with knives.

526
00:24:00,014 --> 00:24:03,1
Relax, Dan,
these knives aren't for Trixie.

527
00:24:04,031 --> 00:24:05,2
They're for a baby.

528
00:24:07,065 --> 00:24:08,5
Okay, new rule.

529
00:24:09,015 --> 00:24:12,6
No more knife play of any kind
with my kid. You got it?

530
00:24:12,070 --> 00:24:14,9
-Fine.
-Trixie, it's time to go.

531
00:24:15,028 --> 00:24:16,1
Grab your stuff.

532
00:24:16,083 --> 00:24:18,8
So who pissed in your Cheerios?

533
00:24:18,095 --> 00:24:20,7
You're even grumpier than usual.

534
00:24:21,037 --> 00:24:24,0
It's the case, okay? I feel powerless.

535
00:24:24,017 --> 00:24:26,3
Any second now,
another person could get killed

536
00:24:26,042 --> 00:24:28,8
and we're just...
we're sitting on our asses.

537
00:24:29,030 --> 00:24:31,3
-Why?
-Because we've got to wait for a judge

538
00:24:31,047 --> 00:24:32,8
to give us a stupid warrant.

539
00:24:36,034 --> 00:24:37,5
Says who?

540
00:24:48,040 --> 00:24:50,7
Mr. Morningstar,
thank you for reaching out.

541
00:24:51,003 --> 00:24:51,9
Are you okay?

542
00:24:52,074 --> 00:24:55,0
Did Detective Decker...
Did she do something?

543
00:24:55,011 --> 00:24:55,9
No.

544
00:24:56,057 --> 00:24:57,4
And she never will.

545
00:24:57,062 --> 00:25:00,3
I'm just here to tell you
that you're wrong about the Detective.

546
00:25:00,091 --> 00:25:02,8
If she's planning anything,
it's an apology.

547
00:25:03,091 --> 00:25:06,1
I certainly hope that that's the case.

548
00:25:06,025 --> 00:25:08,7
Oh, ye of little faith, Father.

549
00:25:10,096 --> 00:25:12,7
Have you noticed her carrying a vial?

550
00:25:14,059 --> 00:25:15,4
A what?

551
00:25:15,093 --> 00:25:17,6
[Father] A vial. It's a...

552
00:25:17,093 --> 00:25:20,3
An ornate thing.
It's about the size of a plum.

553
00:25:21,039 --> 00:25:24,4
I got word from a colleague of mine
in Rome that she'd met with a priest

554
00:25:24,056 --> 00:25:27,6
who was hell-bent
on banishing the devil from Earth.

555
00:25:28,052 --> 00:25:31,3
And you all get paid to do this?
I'm genuinely asking.

556
00:25:32,003 --> 00:25:35,7
Supposedly, this priest has uncovered
a ceremony that would, and bear with me...

557
00:25:36,045 --> 00:25:39,1
trap the devil in hell for all eternity.

558
00:25:39,062 --> 00:25:42,7
He shared the details of this ceremony
with Chloe.

559
00:25:43,058 --> 00:25:44,5
[giggles]

560
00:25:45,016 --> 00:25:49,4
A ceremony to banish the devil to hell?
That is priceless. Ha-ha!

561
00:25:49,050 --> 00:25:50,3
No, seriously,

562
00:25:50,046 --> 00:25:54,1
you all need to take  End of Days
out of the Vatican movie night rotation.

563
00:25:55,022 --> 00:25:56,7
Definitely not one of Arnold's best.

564
00:25:56,084 --> 00:25:57,6
I know.

565
00:25:57,076 --> 00:25:59,1
I know it sounds crazy.

566
00:25:59,076 --> 00:26:03,1
But Chloe was very distressed
last time I saw her.

567
00:26:03,060 --> 00:26:07,7
Apparently, the ceremony involves
giving the subject a sacramental liquid...

568
00:26:08,023 --> 00:26:09,6
that would sedate the devil.

569
00:26:10,044 --> 00:26:11,9
Ooh, let me guess.

570
00:26:12,007 --> 00:26:13,6
It's inside the plum vial.

571
00:26:14,007 --> 00:26:15,0
So I'm told.

572
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:18,9
And if it would sedate the devil,
I fear that it involves some poison.

573
00:26:19,011 --> 00:26:21,9
Something that would kill a normal man.

574
00:26:22,024 --> 00:26:23,9
You're incorrigible, aren't you?

575
00:26:24,004 --> 00:26:26,7
Do you honestly think
that I would travel thousands of miles,

576
00:26:26,083 --> 00:26:30,0
tell you these outlandish tales,
if I didn't take them seriously?

577
00:26:31,021 --> 00:26:33,1
I hope beyond hope that I am wrong.

578
00:26:33,092 --> 00:26:36,6
But if there is any chance
that Chloe could try something,

579
00:26:37,005 --> 00:26:38,6
you need to be careful.

580
00:26:39,026 --> 00:26:41,6
Well, consider me warned.

581
00:26:42,014 --> 00:26:45,5
You may absolve yourself of any further
responsibility in this matter.

582
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:47,1
Now, if you'll excuse me...

583
00:26:48,006 --> 00:26:48,8
I have plans.

584
00:26:56,007 --> 00:26:56,9
[door rattles]

585
00:26:58,045 --> 00:26:59,6
Is that the man?

586
00:27:00,028 --> 00:27:01,7
Not a man, Your Excellency.

587
00:27:02,087 --> 00:27:04,3
The prophecy is real.

588
00:27:05,083 --> 00:27:07,4
And now that the trap is set...

589
00:27:09,004 --> 00:27:10,7
everything will come together soon.

590
00:27:20,026 --> 00:27:24,2
I hope this so-called surprise of yours
doesn't involve me taking off my shoes.

591
00:27:25,001 --> 00:27:27,8
I should warn you
that what I have planned...

592
00:27:28,060 --> 00:27:30,2
might be painful for you, but...

593
00:27:30,077 --> 00:27:33,3
I think, ultimately,
you'll see it's a good thing.

594
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,4
Painful?

595
00:27:34,056 --> 00:27:36,6
Detective,
what on Earth are you talking about?

596
00:27:36,069 --> 00:27:38,2
It's just up ahead.

597
00:27:39,003 --> 00:27:39,9
What is?

598
00:27:42,091 --> 00:27:44,7
Just... forgive me.

599
00:27:46,087 --> 00:27:47,7
Detective...

600
00:27:49,004 --> 00:27:50,2
where are you taking me?

601
00:27:52,062 --> 00:27:54,0
[banging on metal]

602
00:27:56,009 --> 00:27:58,4
[menacing rap playing in background]

603
00:27:58,076 --> 00:27:59,7
Howdy.

604
00:28:01,063 --> 00:28:03,1
What's up, fellas?

605
00:28:04,014 --> 00:28:05,3
[door bangs shut]

606
00:28:07,068 --> 00:28:09,3
Do you have any idea where you are?

607
00:28:10,014 --> 00:28:11,1
Yes, I do.

608
00:28:11,085 --> 00:28:12,9
Los Xs headquarters.

609
00:28:13,048 --> 00:28:16,1
So-called brain trust
of your transnational drug operation.

610
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:17,7
[Dan laughs] Come on, guys, relax.

611
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:19,6
That's not why I'm here, okay?

612
00:28:20,049 --> 00:28:22,9
Susan Ochoa and David Ramirez
were murdered.

613
00:28:23,045 --> 00:28:26,4
And I know you guys are involved somehow.

614
00:28:26,099 --> 00:28:29,7
So I need to talk to the guy or the girl
who's in charge.

615
00:28:30,070 --> 00:28:32,7
And be quick about it.
I'm in a bit of a hurry.

616
00:28:33,083 --> 00:28:34,7
[chuckles]

617
00:28:34,079 --> 00:28:37,0
Okay, you know what,
maybe I didn't make myself clear.

618
00:28:38,013 --> 00:28:41,3
Which one of you losers is in charge?

619
00:28:43,068 --> 00:28:45,3
Okay. Alright.

620
00:28:45,097 --> 00:28:48,3
I guess I'm just going to have
to press the issue, right?

621
00:28:48,089 --> 00:28:50,3
-[clank]
-[boom]

622
00:28:50,047 --> 00:28:52,3
-[Dan] Come on!
-[someone whistles]

623
00:28:54,031 --> 00:28:56,2
You see now, that wasn't so hard, was it?

624
00:28:58,006 --> 00:29:01,7
[Dan] What's up? Can you please tell me
everything you know about the murders?

625
00:29:02,015 --> 00:29:02,9
What if I don't?

626
00:29:03,007 --> 00:29:04,8
Well, then there's going to be a problem.

627
00:29:05,024 --> 00:29:06,8
[laughs wheezily]

628
00:29:08,062 --> 00:29:12,8
Ah, you're a crazy pig, aren't you?
Respeto.

629
00:29:13,091 --> 00:29:15,4
But the only problem we got...

630
00:29:16,012 --> 00:29:18,8
is figuring out
what we're going to do with your body.

631
00:29:18,092 --> 00:29:20,6
Ssss!  Matalo!

632
00:29:20,075 --> 00:29:22,2
[gun cocks]

633
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,5
[whistle]

634
00:29:23,063 --> 00:29:24,8
[crash]

635
00:29:25,034 --> 00:29:27,3
[groaning]

636
00:29:29,035 --> 00:29:30,5
What? What?

637
00:29:38,002 --> 00:29:40,2
[groaning]

638
00:29:45,061 --> 00:29:47,3
Cut it a little close there,
don't you think?

639
00:29:47,070 --> 00:29:49,0
My timing is perfect.

640
00:29:58,071 --> 00:29:59,6
[woman screams]

641
00:30:01,054 --> 00:30:03,2
[groaning]

642
00:30:16,039 --> 00:30:18,0
[metal door clangs]

643
00:30:18,010 --> 00:30:19,2
[men] Let's go.

644
00:30:25,044 --> 00:30:27,5
What are we doing in a soup kitchen?

645
00:30:27,082 --> 00:30:30,4
Volunteering.
You should try it. It could be fun.

646
00:30:30,074 --> 00:30:33,4
Watching people trip and fall is fun.
This...

647
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:35,2
not fun.

648
00:30:36,050 --> 00:30:40,1
Lucifer, I just thought it would be nice
for us to do something good for a change.

649
00:30:40,021 --> 00:30:44,2
Oh, for a change. And just what exactly
is it you'd like me to change?

650
00:30:44,034 --> 00:30:46,1
Oh, Lucifer, that's not what I meant.

651
00:30:46,067 --> 00:30:49,0
Listen, okay, if you'd like to leave,
we can leave.

652
00:30:52,085 --> 00:30:55,5
You have been acting very strange,
Detective.

653
00:30:55,097 --> 00:30:58,8
Wanting me to drink less,
be nicer to suspects, be more...

654
00:30:58,094 --> 00:31:00,5
-[phone buzzes]
-...more philanthropic.

655
00:31:00,065 --> 00:31:02,1
Oh, that's not true.

656
00:31:02,056 --> 00:31:04,9
The only thing that's true
is that you've been lying to me.

657
00:31:05,032 --> 00:31:06,4
No, I haven't.

658
00:31:06,094 --> 00:31:07,8
Show me your purse.

659
00:31:07,090 --> 00:31:08,7
My purse?

660
00:31:09,024 --> 00:31:10,7
-Why?
-Show it to me.

661
00:31:10,086 --> 00:31:11,7
Okay.

662
00:31:12,057 --> 00:31:13,7
Fine.

663
00:31:21,067 --> 00:31:22,8
Detective, what's this?

664
00:31:24,050 --> 00:31:25,3
Nothing.

665
00:31:25,042 --> 00:31:28,3
Oh, right. Well, if it's nothing,
you won't mind me drinking it, will you?

666
00:31:28,046 --> 00:31:30,8
-No, don't drink it. It's perfume.
-I've had worse.

667
00:31:30,097 --> 00:31:32,5
[Chloe yells] No, don't!

668
00:31:34,051 --> 00:31:36,8
I know you've been meeting
with Father Kinley.

669
00:31:38,022 --> 00:31:39,4
I know all about it.

670
00:31:40,039 --> 00:31:41,9
-It's not what you think.
-Isn't it?

671
00:31:42,002 --> 00:31:45,4
-[phone buzzes]
-No, it's not. It's...

672
00:31:45,048 --> 00:31:47,1
[Chloe gasps]

673
00:31:48,015 --> 00:31:51,0
Dan, can I call you back?
I'm right in the middle of something.

674
00:31:51,011 --> 00:31:52,5
[Dan]  I know who the killer is.

675
00:31:52,078 --> 00:31:53,6
[Chloe]  What?

676
00:31:53,082 --> 00:31:55,2
And he's about to skip town.

677
00:32:16,001 --> 00:32:17,8
[phone buzzes]

678
00:32:17,093 --> 00:32:18,8
[Chloe] Hey, Dan.

679
00:32:18,093 --> 00:32:21,5
[Dan]  Okay, his name is Oscar
and I just sent you a picture.

680
00:32:23,060 --> 00:32:26,8
[Chloe] It's Susan Ochoa's drug counselor.
We talked to him at the scene.

681
00:32:26,090 --> 00:32:29,1
Well, the head of Los Xs
says that he's the killer.

682
00:32:29,028 --> 00:32:30,5
The head of Los Xs?

683
00:32:31,007 --> 00:32:32,0
How?

684
00:32:32,015 --> 00:32:33,9
We caught a break, okay?
It doesn't matter.

685
00:32:33,099 --> 00:32:36,8
What matters is that Rivas
was a gang counselor for both victims.

686
00:32:36,095 --> 00:32:38,4
So you're saying they trusted him,

687
00:32:38,053 --> 00:32:42,3
made their dark sides vulnerable
and then he just stabbed them in the back.

688
00:32:42,046 --> 00:32:43,6
Yeah, pretty much.

689
00:32:44,033 --> 00:32:45,2
Why?

690
00:32:45,029 --> 00:32:46,9
That's the million-dollar question.

691
00:32:47,050 --> 00:32:49,7
[fast-paced music playing]

692
00:32:55,072 --> 00:32:56,8
[Chloe] Lucifer!

693
00:32:57,043 --> 00:32:58,4
Lucifer, wait!

694
00:32:58,055 --> 00:32:59,3
[crash]

695
00:33:02,081 --> 00:33:03,8
-Wait!
-[door slams]

696
00:33:03,094 --> 00:33:05,6
[banging on door]

697
00:33:05,069 --> 00:33:06,9
-Let me in!
-[metal creaking]

698
00:33:07,006 --> 00:33:10,1
[banging on door]

699
00:33:17,041 --> 00:33:18,4
[Lucifer, rasping] You!

700
00:33:18,053 --> 00:33:20,1
How could you just murder them?

701
00:33:21,045 --> 00:33:22,7
I did what needed to be done.

702
00:33:23,041 --> 00:33:24,2
[bang]

703
00:33:24,037 --> 00:33:25,7
-[groans]
-[crash]

704
00:33:25,083 --> 00:33:27,7
[Lucifer panting] They trusted you!

705
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:31,6
They shared their darkest truths
and you just betray them?

706
00:33:31,071 --> 00:33:32,5
[Oscar gasps]

707
00:33:32,088 --> 00:33:35,2
And I would happily do it again.

708
00:33:35,034 --> 00:33:37,8
Oh, ho ho! This is going to be fun.

709
00:33:38,014 --> 00:33:40,5
-[Lucifer roars]
-[smashing of wood]

710
00:33:42,002 --> 00:33:44,7
I showed those losers the real me.

711
00:33:44,081 --> 00:33:47,1
Careful, or I'll show you the real me.

712
00:33:47,019 --> 00:33:49,2
Oh, yes. Do it!

713
00:33:50,094 --> 00:33:52,4
I thought they could change.

714
00:33:53,028 --> 00:33:54,3
But they couldn't.

715
00:33:55,011 --> 00:33:56,6
Dave was stealing again.

716
00:33:57,007 --> 00:33:58,7
Susan was back on drugs.

717
00:33:58,099 --> 00:33:59,9
They were trash.

718
00:34:00,062 --> 00:34:01,6
So I killed them.

719
00:34:02,074 --> 00:34:03,5
[laughs]

720
00:34:03,066 --> 00:34:04,7
What are you going to do?

721
00:34:04,095 --> 00:34:06,8
-[bang]
-[Oscar gasps]

722
00:34:06,091 --> 00:34:08,8
[Oscar laughs demonically]

723
00:34:08,092 --> 00:34:09,8
I'll show you.

724
00:34:09,092 --> 00:34:11,3
Show me what you've got.

725
00:34:11,046 --> 00:34:12,5
Come on, Lucifer.

726
00:34:13,030 --> 00:34:14,8
Show us who you really are.

727
00:34:18,026 --> 00:34:19,5
[thump]

728
00:34:19,059 --> 00:34:20,9
[Oscar panting]

729
00:34:21,047 --> 00:34:22,7
Do you want me to punish you?

730
00:34:24,027 --> 00:34:25,6
-Why?
-[Chloe] Hands in the air.

731
00:34:29,069 --> 00:34:30,6
I failed.

732
00:34:32,057 --> 00:34:33,7
May God forgive me.

733
00:34:35,007 --> 00:34:36,8
-[groans]
-[splintering sound]

734
00:34:39,041 --> 00:34:41,3
[Dan]
Yeah, that's what I'm talking about, man.

735
00:34:41,041 --> 00:34:44,7
When you kneed that dude
and he fell down and I just came in there,

736
00:34:44,079 --> 00:34:47,1
wham, elbow to the face, amazing.

737
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,8
It just felt so good, you know.

738
00:34:49,096 --> 00:34:52,8
Just to let loose,
not have to follow the rules for a change.

739
00:34:53,034 --> 00:34:55,8
And you are amazing...

740
00:34:56,042 --> 00:34:57,5
for helping me out like that.

741
00:34:57,076 --> 00:34:59,5
Come on, any time
you want to beat someone up.

742
00:34:59,068 --> 00:35:01,7
Any time, you call me.

743
00:35:01,084 --> 00:35:04,1
In fact, I'm going to kick your ass
if you don't.

744
00:35:04,026 --> 00:35:06,1
Oh, man, this is going to sound crazy.

745
00:35:06,093 --> 00:35:08,3
But I can't wait to do it again.

746
00:35:08,060 --> 00:35:11,5
Oh! Old Dan is back.

747
00:35:12,027 --> 00:35:13,4
I am so in.

748
00:35:13,056 --> 00:35:15,6
The straight and narrow Dan,
total buzzkill.

749
00:35:16,028 --> 00:35:17,6
Screw that Dan.

750
00:35:18,036 --> 00:35:19,6
It was getting me nowhere.

751
00:35:19,070 --> 00:35:21,7
Trust me, darker Dan...

752
00:35:22,032 --> 00:35:23,5
will get you real far.

753
00:35:28,054 --> 00:35:30,3
Well, that does it.

754
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,5
I'll never be able to eat beef kebabs
ever again.

755
00:35:36,092 --> 00:35:37,9
Did you find anything?

756
00:35:38,038 --> 00:35:42,3
[Ella] Yeah, same thing. Bloody clothes,
another knife, same as the others.

757
00:35:42,047 --> 00:35:43,6
And who owns the house?

758
00:35:43,072 --> 00:35:46,3
I don't know, 
I'll see if we have that yet. Man...

759
00:35:46,072 --> 00:35:49,7
this dude must have been really
scared of something to go out like that.

760
00:35:50,035 --> 00:35:52,2
[Chloe] Mm. Or someone.

761
00:35:57,094 --> 00:35:58,8
Are you okay?

762
00:35:59,069 --> 00:36:01,2
Something else was happening here.

763
00:36:02,011 --> 00:36:03,1
Something strange.

764
00:36:05,012 --> 00:36:08,6
He knew about my true face.
He wanted me to show it to him.

765
00:36:09,020 --> 00:36:10,4
-Why?
-I don't know.

766
00:36:11,016 --> 00:36:16,0
But I could have sworn
that he said, "Show us your face."

767
00:36:16,017 --> 00:36:17,0
[Chloe] Us?

768
00:36:17,017 --> 00:36:18,5
But there was no-one else here.

769
00:36:22,026 --> 00:36:23,9
Unless it's a two-way mirror.

770
00:36:24,022 --> 00:36:26,6
[splintering of glass]

771
00:36:30,010 --> 00:36:34,1
[Ella] Erm, that was evidence.
This is a secure crime scene.

772
00:36:35,035 --> 00:36:36,3
Never mind.

773
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,3
You're never going to believe
who owns the house.

774
00:36:41,024 --> 00:36:42,5
The Catholic Church.

775
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:47,3
Your friend Father Kinley
must have been watching.

776
00:36:47,083 --> 00:36:50,4
I think Kinley arranged all of this
to get to you.

777
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:53,6
He wanted to show someone who...

778
00:36:54,042 --> 00:36:55,2
or what...

779
00:36:56,033 --> 00:36:57,7
you really are.

780
00:36:58,017 --> 00:37:01,3
I know that we have a lot to talk about
and I have a lot to explain

781
00:37:01,038 --> 00:37:04,2
and I know a lot of this is my fault,
but you need to trust me right now.

782
00:37:04,034 --> 00:37:06,3
Oh! Really?

783
00:37:06,047 --> 00:37:09,0
-I think you're in real danger.
-Enlighten me, Detective.

784
00:37:10,006 --> 00:37:12,2
Just who exactly am I in danger from?

785
00:37:16,065 --> 00:37:18,6
What in God's name was that?

786
00:37:19,032 --> 00:37:20,5
It was a setback, that's all.

787
00:37:21,003 --> 00:37:24,3
That man killed two people,
then himself, and you knew?

788
00:37:24,045 --> 00:37:27,1
No, wait. You orchestrated it.

789
00:37:28,057 --> 00:37:30,0
Extreme measures were taken.

790
00:37:30,079 --> 00:37:33,6
It would have been worth it
if Lucifer had shown his true face.

791
00:37:33,091 --> 00:37:35,4
Can you even hear yourself?

792
00:37:35,050 --> 00:37:39,7
The Church needs to see that
Lucifer Morningstar is the actual devil.

793
00:37:39,088 --> 00:37:41,2
[distant footsteps]

794
00:37:41,034 --> 00:37:42,3
It should have worked.

795
00:37:43,005 --> 00:37:45,4
Chloe told me that he likes to make
every case about himself

796
00:37:45,055 --> 00:37:48,6
and I set it up perfectly
for him to want to punish Rivas.

797
00:37:49,064 --> 00:37:51,0
How could he not reveal himself?

798
00:37:51,056 --> 00:37:53,8
[Chloe] Because he's better
than you give him credit for.

799
00:37:54,010 --> 00:37:55,0
[laughs]

800
00:37:55,023 --> 00:37:56,2
Detective Decker.

801
00:37:56,089 --> 00:37:59,6
Well, she knows the truth. Tell him.

802
00:38:00,019 --> 00:38:01,6
I do know the truth, Father.

803
00:38:02,032 --> 00:38:05,4
You worked at the same parish
in El Salvador as Oscar Rivas.

804
00:38:06,045 --> 00:38:07,8
It's quite the coincidence.

805
00:38:08,011 --> 00:38:12,1
Oscar was a good man, a true believer,
willing to do what was necessary.

806
00:38:13,037 --> 00:38:16,0
To take what action was needed
to battle evil.

807
00:38:16,054 --> 00:38:20,2
You had Rivas kill two innocent people
to battle evil?

808
00:38:21,013 --> 00:38:23,3
He willingly sacrificed himself

809
00:38:23,038 --> 00:38:28,3
to force Lucifer to reveal his true form,
to show the Church finally the truth.

810
00:38:29,005 --> 00:38:30,2
[Father scoffs]

811
00:38:31,014 --> 00:38:33,8
This is all your own private crusade,
isn't it, Father?

812
00:38:33,093 --> 00:38:35,7
The Vatican doesn't know about this,
do they?

813
00:38:36,002 --> 00:38:36,8
[laughs]

814
00:38:38,023 --> 00:38:39,9
Because they don't believe.

815
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:43,7
But, together,
you and I can convince them.

816
00:38:44,098 --> 00:38:46,4
Together, we can save them.

817
00:38:47,003 --> 00:38:48,1
And so many others.

818
00:38:48,061 --> 00:38:50,0
[clink of handcuffs]

819
00:38:50,016 --> 00:38:51,2
You're under arrest, Father.

820
00:38:52,012 --> 00:38:53,5
For conspiracy to commit murder.

821
00:38:54,024 --> 00:38:55,4
Dear, dear girl...

822
00:38:56,004 --> 00:38:59,1
Oscar is dead
and I have done nothing wrong myself.

823
00:38:59,025 --> 00:39:00,2
You have no proof.

824
00:39:00,092 --> 00:39:02,3
It's your word against mine.

825
00:39:02,079 --> 00:39:05,5
-[handcuffs clink]
-There is always evidence.

826
00:39:06,013 --> 00:39:09,7
I will find it and I won't stop
until there's enough to put you away.

827
00:39:09,093 --> 00:39:11,1
[Vicar] That won't be necessary.

828
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:14,1
I'll testify. Anything you need.

829
00:39:18,023 --> 00:39:20,3
I'm sorry, but you're sick, Will.

830
00:39:28,036 --> 00:39:29,5
[female voice] Mrs. Smith.

831
00:39:30,045 --> 00:39:32,0
I'm looking for Mrs. Smith.

832
00:39:39,008 --> 00:39:40,0
Amenadiel.

833
00:39:41,025 --> 00:39:42,5
What are you doing here?

834
00:39:42,058 --> 00:39:44,2
Linda, you don't have to do this alone.

835
00:39:45,013 --> 00:39:48,5
I want to be here for this baby and, most
importantly, I want to be here for you.

836
00:39:50,063 --> 00:39:51,8
Erm...

837
00:39:52,047 --> 00:39:53,6
Yeah.

838
00:39:56,010 --> 00:39:57,0
[Linda] Oh.

839
00:40:03,073 --> 00:40:05,1
Will you marry me?

840
00:40:05,019 --> 00:40:06,1
[surprised giggles]

841
00:40:06,044 --> 00:40:07,6
[laughs]

842
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:10,5
[Linda inhales, whispers] No.

843
00:40:10,061 --> 00:40:12,1
[woman gasps in background]

844
00:40:13,053 --> 00:40:15,4
[quietly] No.

845
00:40:16,083 --> 00:40:17,9
No. Amenadiel...

846
00:40:18,024 --> 00:40:19,2
Amenadiel, come here.

847
00:40:19,095 --> 00:40:20,9
See...

848
00:40:21,004 --> 00:40:22,1
Amenadiel...

849
00:40:24,021 --> 00:40:29,2
What you're doing is amazing
and heroic and I should be so lucky...

850
00:40:29,092 --> 00:40:32,9
to end up with someone
half as special as you are.

851
00:40:34,014 --> 00:40:36,3
But what you're doing here, it's...

852
00:40:39,064 --> 00:40:41,5
It's for the wrong reasons.

853
00:40:43,023 --> 00:40:44,1
And it's...

854
00:40:44,069 --> 00:40:46,1
It's not what I...

855
00:40:46,027 --> 00:40:48,1
It's not what I need right now.

856
00:40:49,044 --> 00:40:50,5
And what do you need?

857
00:40:54,003 --> 00:40:56,0
I think I just need someone
to hold my hand

858
00:40:56,053 --> 00:40:58,2
and tell me everything's going to be okay.

859
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,3
I promise you, Linda...

860
00:41:07,059 --> 00:41:09,1
everything is going to be okay.

861
00:41:10,046 --> 00:41:11,3
[sighs]

862
00:41:23,006 --> 00:41:24,2
[bell rings]

863
00:41:29,032 --> 00:41:30,1
Hi.

864
00:41:35,049 --> 00:41:37,3
I arrested Father Kinley,

865
00:41:37,041 --> 00:41:40,0
so you don't have to worry about him
coming after you anymore.

866
00:41:42,024 --> 00:41:44,4
I don't care
that he was trying to hurt me.

867
00:41:46,021 --> 00:41:47,2
I care that you were.

868
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:50,3
[sighs]

869
00:41:50,071 --> 00:41:52,9
Lucifer, you have to understand that...

870
00:41:54,026 --> 00:41:55,8
after I saw you...

871
00:41:57,084 --> 00:41:58,8
saw your face...

872
00:42:00,064 --> 00:42:02,2
I had to get away...

873
00:42:02,085 --> 00:42:04,2
to process things...

874
00:42:04,093 --> 00:42:05,7
you know?

875
00:42:07,006 --> 00:42:10,4
And somehow I ended up in Rome.

876
00:42:11,082 --> 00:42:12,8
Kinley found me...

877
00:42:13,053 --> 00:42:16,7
and obviously
I shouldn't have confided in him, but...

878
00:42:17,036 --> 00:42:19,2
[sighs] you know, at the time...

879
00:42:19,082 --> 00:42:22,0
it felt like he understood
what I was going through.

880
00:42:22,033 --> 00:42:24,5
-He said you found him.
-He's lying.

881
00:42:29,012 --> 00:42:30,8
There's a lot of that going around.

882
00:42:31,050 --> 00:42:32,7
Well, yes...

883
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:34,3
I...

884
00:42:35,088 --> 00:42:38,0
[voice wavers] I did lie to you...

885
00:42:38,043 --> 00:42:43,2
and for a moment, I was helping him
try to send you back to hell.

886
00:42:43,072 --> 00:42:44,5
[scoffs]

887
00:42:45,064 --> 00:42:47,8
How could you do that to me? To me?

888
00:42:47,089 --> 00:42:49,8
[screaming] Because I'm terrified!

889
00:42:53,036 --> 00:42:54,4
[gasps]

890
00:42:54,053 --> 00:42:55,9
You are the...

891
00:42:56,061 --> 00:42:58,4
actual devil.

892
00:42:58,053 --> 00:42:59,4
I mean...

893
00:43:02,058 --> 00:43:09,3
every story of good and bad
from throughout history, throughout time,

894
00:43:09,046 --> 00:43:13,9
says that you are the embodiment of evil.

895
00:43:14,059 --> 00:43:16,5
[Chloe gasps, sobbing]

896
00:43:16,063 --> 00:43:20,3
And how am I, Chloe Decker, a nobody...

897
00:43:21,018 --> 00:43:22,8
supposed to deal with that?

898
00:43:32,081 --> 00:43:33,8
But...

899
00:43:34,073 --> 00:43:35,6
But then...

900
00:43:38,082 --> 00:43:39,8
Then I came back.

901
00:43:41,095 --> 00:43:42,7
And...

902
00:43:43,057 --> 00:43:44,6
[sighs]

903
00:43:45,041 --> 00:43:46,4
And I saw you.

904
00:43:48,025 --> 00:43:49,7
I really saw you.

905
00:43:52,075 --> 00:43:54,7
And I remembered how you made me feel.

906
00:43:57,013 --> 00:43:59,9
And I realized, Lucifer,
you're not that guy.

907
00:44:00,067 --> 00:44:01,5
No.

908
00:44:03,076 --> 00:44:05,4
What if I am that guy?

909
00:44:06,051 --> 00:44:09,1
You don't have to be. You could change.

910
00:44:09,027 --> 00:44:10,6
But what if I can't?

911
00:44:13,069 --> 00:44:14,8
[gasps]

912
00:44:16,032 --> 00:44:18,0
Could you accept me like this?

913
00:44:20,015 --> 00:44:21,9
I... oh...

914
00:44:22,057 --> 00:44:26,4
You have no idea how much I want to.

915
00:44:27,003 --> 00:44:28,7
I do. I'm...

916
00:44:29,024 --> 00:44:30,0
I'm trying.

917
00:44:30,016 --> 00:44:31,1
But could you?

918
00:44:31,091 --> 00:44:36,7
[sniffs, stammers, sobs]

919
00:44:37,013 --> 00:44:38,3
I don't know.

920
00:44:40,063 --> 00:44:41,4
[sniffs]

921
00:44:42,080 --> 00:44:44,0
Then I have my answer.

922
00:44:48,076 --> 00:44:49,6
[gasps]

923
00:45:13,058 --> 00:45:16,5
[inaudible]

924
00:45:28,093 --> 00:45:29,8
Your Excellency.

925
00:45:30,064 --> 00:45:32,8
Did you change your mind?
Are you here to get me out?

926
00:45:33,048 --> 00:45:35,0
I am here to take your confession.

927
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:37,9
I have nothing to confess.

928
00:45:37,098 --> 00:45:41,9
William, you are responsible
for the deaths of three people. For what?

929
00:45:42,003 --> 00:45:43,9
I'm trying to save lives.

930
00:45:44,049 --> 00:45:45,9
To stop the prophecy.

931
00:45:46,082 --> 00:45:50,9
When the devil walks the earth and finds
his first love, evil shall be released.

932
00:45:51,003 --> 00:45:53,7
Enough with this damned prophecy
you're obsessed with.

933
00:45:53,087 --> 00:45:55,9
The devil is walking the earth.

934
00:45:56,004 --> 00:45:57,7
His Holiness has issued an order.

935
00:45:58,075 --> 00:46:00,1
You've been excommunicated.

936
00:46:04,055 --> 00:46:05,4
I...

937
00:46:05,092 --> 00:46:10,7
may have failed, temporarily,
to prove that Lucifer is the devil,

938
00:46:11,014 --> 00:46:13,7
but at least I have pushed him
and Chloe Decker apart.

939
00:46:13,085 --> 00:46:16,3
Maybe that will be enough
to stop the prophecy.

940
00:46:18,090 --> 00:46:22,4
Even if Lucifer Morningstar was the devil

941
00:46:22,069 --> 00:46:24,4
and the prophecy was true...

942
00:46:25,061 --> 00:46:28,9
what makes you so sure
Chloe Decker is even his first love?

943
00:46:37,050 --> 00:46:39,7
I'll be praying for you, William.

944
00:46:46,022 --> 00:46:47,3
[door buzzes]

945
00:46:47,038 --> 00:46:48,2
Of course she is.

946
00:46:49,051 --> 00:46:50,7
Who else could it be?

947
00:46:50,084 --> 00:46:55,0
["Glory Box" by Portishead
playing in background]

948
00:47:04,027 --> 00:47:05,5
[sighs]

949
00:47:07,032 --> 00:47:08,5
So many options.

950
00:47:13,033 --> 00:47:14,2
I'll have...

951
00:47:16,054 --> 00:47:17,5
an appletini.

